The paper deals with computational problems in geometric intersection graphs, which are often studied in the subfields of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The main focus of the paper is on the homomorphism problem, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and is studied in various subfields of computer science, including algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), and graph theory (cs.GT).
